{"id":442370,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Clary","text":"Robert Clary (born Robert Max Widerman; March 1, 1926) is a French-American actor, writer and lecturer. He is best known for his role as Corporal LeBeau (\"Frenchie\") in the television sitcom \"Hogan's Heroes\". He is the last surviving main cast member since the death of Cynthia Lynn in March 2014.\nClary was born in Paris. He is Jewish and survived the Buchenwald concentration camp in Weimar, Germany during the Holocaust of World War II.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"French_people","surface_form":"French","offset":60},{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":67},{"uri":"Actor","surface_form":"actor","offset":76},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":83},{"uri":"Lecturer","surface_form":"lecturer","offset":94},{"uri":"Television","surface_form":"television","offset":173},{"uri":"Situation_comedy","surface_form":"sitcom","offset":184},{"uri":"Hogan%27s_Heroes","surface_form":"Hogan's Heroes","offset":192},{"uri":"Cynthia_Lynn","surface_form":"Cynthia Lynn","offset":270},{"uri":"Paris","surface_form":"Paris","offset":316},{"uri":"Jewish","surface_form":"Jewish","offset":329},{"uri":"Buchenwald_concentration_camp","surface_form":"Buchenwald concentration camp","offset":353},{"uri":"Weimar","surface_form":"Weimar","offset":386},{"uri":"Germany","surface_form":"Germany","offset":394},{"uri":"Holocaust","surface_form":"Holocaust","offset":413},{"uri":"World_War_II","surface_form":"World War II","offset":426}]}